# Perl::Critic config for nix-cpan (CI lints nix-cpan.pl with it).

# The codebase uses Perl signatures pervasively (`sub f ($x, @rest) { ... }`,
# enabled by `use v5.42`). This Perl::Critic version parses a signature as a
# subroutine prototype and flags every one — a false positive. We never use real
# prototypes, so disable the policy rather than litter the code with `## no critic`.
[-Subroutines::ProhibitSubroutinePrototypes]
